# Axis 7 — deep handler reinstall over recursion

A single handler is re-entered on every recursive step: each `Amb.flip()` in the
recursion suspends to the same handler and resumes (§14.1 "deep handler
reinstall"). Verifies the handler stays installed across the recursive suffix and
each perform routes to it.

```scalascript
effect Amb:
  def flip(): Boolean

def prog(n: Int): Int =
  if n == 0 then 0 else
    val b = Amb.flip()
    (if b then 1 else 0) + prog(n - 1)

val r = handle(prog(3)) {
  case Amb.flip(resume) => resume(true)
  case Return(x) => x
}
println(r)
```
